<section aria-label="Why Chicago businesses wrap their fleets" id="pain-points-statement" style="background:#111;border-top:3px solid #FFD700;border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:64px 32px;text-align:center">
<div style="max-width:960px;margin:0 auto">
<p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.7rem;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:16px">The Problem Every Chicago Fleet Operator Knows</p>
<h2 style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:20px">Your Vans Are Already on the Road. They're Just Not Working for You.</h2>
<p style="font-size:1.05rem;color:#ccc;line-height:1.8;max-width:760px;margin:0 auto 48px">Every unwrapped service van driving Chicago's neighborhoods is a missed impression. Every white panel without a phone number is a call that went to a competitor. And every cheap wrap that peeled after one winter is money spent twice. You need graphics that survive Chicago's freeze-thaw cycles, communicate your brand at 40 mph, and pay back the investment in leads — not a logo sticker that looks dated by spring.</p>
<div class="pain-points-grid" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:24px;margin-bottom:48px">
<div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid #2a2a2a;border-top:3px solid #FFD700;padding:28px 24px;text-align:left">
<p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:10px">Pain Point 01 — Branding</p>
<h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px">Invisible Fleet = Lost Leads</h3>
<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#aaa;line-height:1.7">Your trucks are driving 40,000+ impressions per day through the exact neighborhoods you serve. Without brand graphics, every one of those impressions benefits your wrapped competitor — not you.</p>
</div>
<div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid #2a2a2a;border-top:3px solid #FFD700;padding:28px 24px;text-align:left">
<p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:10px">Pain Point 02 — Durability</p>
<h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px">Cheap Vinyl Doesn't Survive Chicago</h3>
<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#aaa;line-height:1.7">Calendered vinyl fails within 18 months in Chicago's freeze-thaw cycles. Peeling edges, lifting seams, fading print — a $1,500 wrap that fails twice costs more than one premium cast vinyl install that runs 6 years.</p>
</div>
<div style="background:#1a1a1a;border:1px solid #2a2a2a;border-top:3px solid #FFD700;padding:28px 24px;text-align:left">
<p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:10px">Pain Point 03 — ROI</p>
<h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px">Most Shops Don't Know the Tax Angle</h3>
<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#aaa;line-height:1.7">Commercial vehicle wraps are IRS Section 179 advertising expenses — 100% deductible in the year of purchase. A $3,750 cargo van wrap in the 28% bracket costs you $2,700 after tax. Most wrap shops never tell you this.</p>
</div>
